<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-569-761  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 569 761.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 23 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sprint offers Mac software, clipping service. (US Sprint)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   US Sprint Communications Co. (Services).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Telephone companiesCommunications Service SuppliersSearchingElectronic mail systemsCommunications softwareProduct Development.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SPRINT OFFERS MAC SOFTWARE, CLIPPING SERVICE SAN FRANCISCO, CALIFORNIA,U.S.A., 1990 OCT 23 (NB) -- SprintMail announced Mac SprintMail, acommunications software package allowing Macintosh PCs to access the serviceeasily, and a news clipping service.andM;Mac SprintMail lets Macintosh users access SprintMail using common Macintoshcommands and the Macintosh interface.andP;  The program is due for release inJanuary, and will allow Mac users to send fax, telex and hard copy messagesas well as mail.andP;  The program also lets users combine ASCII text and binaryfiles in a single message, so schematics could be faxed alongside reporttexts and recipients wouldn't have to re-key the text.andM;The news clipping service filters news from 15 international newswires,scanning 6,000 stories based on keywords input by users.andP;  The stories areautomatically collected in a SprintMail mailbox, which formats anddistributes high-priority stories.andP;  There is no monthly charge for theclipping service -- users are billed only for normal character and accesscharges, as when they're receiving SprintMail messages.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19901023/Press Contact: Robin Pence, US Sprint,202-828-7454)</TEXT></DOC>